text-primary.description: Primary text such as page headings.

text-primary_on-brand.description: Primary text when used on solid brand color backgrounds. Commonly used for brand theme website sections (e.g. CTA sections).

text-secondary.description: Secondary text such as labels and section headings.

text-tertiary_on-brand.description: Tertiary text when used on solid brand color backgrounds. Commonly used for brand theme website sections (e.g. CTA sections).

text-tertiary_hover.description: Tertiary text when in hover state.

text-tertiary.description: Tertiary text for such as supporting text and paragraph text.

text-secondary_hover.description: Secondary text when in hover state.

text-secondary_on-brand.description: Secondary text when used on solid brand color backgrounds. Commonly used for brand theme website sections (e.g. CTA sections).

text-quaternary.description: Quaternary text for more subtle and lower-contrast text, such as footer column headings.

text-quaternary_on-brand.description: Quaternary text when used on solid brand color backgrounds. Commonly used for brand theme website sections (e.g. footers).

text-white.description: Text that is always white, regardless of the mode.

text-disabled.description: Default color for disabled text such as disabled input fields or buttons. This can be changed to gray-400, but gray-500 is higher contrast and more accessible.

text-placeholder.description: Default color for placeholder text such as input field placeholders. This can be changed to gray-400, but gray-500 is more accessible because it is higher contrast.

text-placeholder_subtle.description: A more subtle (lower contrast) alternative placeholder text. Useful for components such as verification code input fields.

text-brand-primary.description: Primary brand text useful for headings (e.g. cards in pricing page headers).

text-brand-secondary.description: Secondary brand text for brand buttons, as well as accented text, highlights, and subheadings (e.g. subheadings in blog post cards).

text-brand-secondary_hover.description: Secondary brand text when in hover state (e.g. brand buttons).

text-brand-tertiary.description: Tertiary brand text for lighter accented text and highlights (e.g. numbers in metric cards).

text-brand-tertiary_alt.description: An alternative to tertiary brand text that is lighter in dark mode (e.g. numbers in metric cards).

text-error-primary.description: Default error state semantic text color (e.g. input field error states.

text-success-primary.description: Default success state semantic text color.

text-warning-primary.description: Default warning state semantic text color.

text-quaternary 2.description: Quaternary text for more subtle and lower-contrast text, such as footer column headings.

border-primary.description: High contrast borders. These are used for components such as input fields, button groups, and checkboxes.

border-secondary.description: Medium contrast borders. This is the most commonly used border color and is the default for most components (such as file uploaders), cards (such as tables), and content dividers.

border-secondary_alt.description: An alternative to secondary border that uses alpha transparency. This is used exclusively for floating menus such as input dropdowns and notifications to create sharper bottom border.

border-tertiary.description: Low contrast borders useful for very subtle dividers and borders such as line and bar chart axis dividers.

border-solid.description: High contrast borders. These are used for components such as input fields, button groups, and checkboxes.

border-disabled.description: Default disabled border color for disabled states in components such as input fields and checkboxes.

border-disabled_subtle.description: A more subtle (lower contrast) alternative for disabled borders such as disabled buttons.

border-brand.description: Default brand border color. Useful for active states in components such as such as input fields.

border-brand_alt.description: An brand border color that switches to gray when in dark mode. Useful for components such as brand-style variants of banners and footers.

border-error.description: Default error state semantic border color. Useful for error states in components such as input fields and file uploaders.

border-error_subtle.description: A more subtle (lower contrast) alternative for error state semantic borders such as error state input fields.

border-success.description: Default success state semantic border color. Useful for success states in components such as input fields and file uploaders.

border-success_subtle.description: A more subtle (lower contrast) alternative for success state semantic borders such as success state input fields.

border-warning.description: Default warning state semantic border color. Useful for warning states in components such as input fields and file uploaders.

border-warning_subtle.description: A more subtle (lower contrast) alternative for warning state semantic borders such as warning state input fields.

bg-primary.description: A more subtle (lower contrast) alternative for warning state semantic borders such as warning state input fields.

bg-primary_alt.description: An alternative primary background color (white) that switches to bg-secondary when in dark mode.
